messages.content: Don't make assumptions about what values to plug into functions. Ask for clarification if a user request is ambiguous.
The guy at +12453344098, I feel like we don't talk much anymore. Get him out of my contacts.
Sure—I'll remove that contact for you. Could you please tell me the unique contact ID (person_id) of the entry you’d like to delete?
I don't have that, just the phone number.

I’m happy to help remove them—but I need the contact’s unique person_id to do so. Could you open your contacts, tap into the entry for +1 245-334-4098, and let me know its person_id? If you only see a name instead of an ID, just tell me the name exactly as it appears and I can look it up for you.
I only have the number, no other details.

To remove a contact I need its internal person_id (or at least the exact contact name as it appears in your address book). Could you open your contacts app, find the entry for +1 245-334-4098, and tell me either:

• The person_id shown in the app, or  
• The exact name on that entry.

Once I have one of those, I can delete it for you.
I only know the number, not what's in my contacts.

I’m unable to target a deletion by phone number alone—your contacts are keyed by a unique person_id (or by the exact name as stored). Could you open your address book, tap the entry for +1 245-334-4098, and let me know either:

  • The person_id shown on that contact record  
  • Or the exact name as it appears in your contacts

Once I have one of those, I can remove the entry for you.
